From: Ian Campbell <Ian.Campbell@citrix.com>
Date: Wed, 31 Aug 2011 00:47:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 01/26] qlcnic: convert to SKB paged frag API.
Patch-mainline: v3.2-rc1
Git-commit: e0ee9b98d5ff10acd7477ea5f0dcaffeb4a999bc
References: bnc#784817 FATE#313899

Signed-off-by: Ian Campbell <ian.campbell@citrix.com>
Cc: Anirban Chakraborty <anirban.chakraborty@qlogic.com>
Cc: Sony Chacko <sony.chacko@qlogic.com>
Cc: linux-driver@qlogic.com
Cc: netdev@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Shahed Shaikh <shahed.shaikh@qlogic.com>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_main.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_main.c
@@ -2135,8 +2135,8 @@ qlcnic_map_tx_skb(struct pci_dev *pdev,
 		frag = &skb_shinfo(skb)->frags[i];
 		nf = &pbuf->frag_array[i+1];
 
-		map = pci_map_page(pdev, frag->page, frag->page_offset,
-				frag->size, PCI_DMA_TODEVICE);
+		map = skb_frag_dma_map(&pdev->dev, frag, 0, frag->size,
+				       PCI_DMA_TODEVICE);
 		if (pci_dma_mapping_error(pdev, map))
 			goto unwind;
 
